<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The genus name is an arbitrary combination of the Latin word 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“phasma”">&quot;phasma&quot;</normalizedToken>
, meaning ghost, which refers to the type 
<normalizedToken originalValue="species’">species'</normalizedToken>
pale appearance and dark habitat, and the genus name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Savigny" authorityYear="1816" class="Crustacea" family="Potamidae" genus="Potamon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Potamon" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Potamon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is the type genus of the family. Gender neuter.
</paragraph>
